        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-08 00:21:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBruno, unfortunately the use of \"set -e\" caused the script to exit with an error before the \"if [[ $? != 0 ]]\" check was done and the rsync fallback was missed. I changed the code to handle this properly.\n\nThis doesn't remove the need to fix whatever problem is causing migrate to fail, but will at least fix the interop problem.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c7acb05d00734234b0e4858cb962d73962f3d205",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2014-01-08 10:45:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOk! I did not know this very special case for \"set -e\". BTW, this is well documented in bash man-page.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
